items.title: Arrieta throws off mound; 'pen session next
items.summary: Cubs pitcher Jake Arrieta threw off a mound on Thursday, but it wasn't a full-fledged bullpen session, which will be the next step in the right-hander's rehab as he works his way back from a right hamstring strain sustained on Sept. 4.

items.title: Lobaton exits after being hit by pitch
items.summary: Nationals catcher Jose Lobaton exited Thursday night's game against the Braves in the second inning after he was struck on the left foot by an errant slider from right-hander Mike Foltynewicz.

items.title: Mets to hold hurricane relief drive at Citi Field
items.summary: The Mets announced that they will hold a hurricane relief drive next week at Citi Field to help those affected in Houston and Florida, in conjunction with Queens borough president Melinda Katz.
